<h4 id="problem">Problem</h4>
<ol>
  <li>minimize  $C^Tx$
    <ul>
      <li>subject to $a_i^T \leq b_i, i=1,\cdots,m$</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>the objective and all constraint functions are linear</li>
  <li>no analytical formula for solution, reliable and efficient algorithms and
software.
    <ul>
      <li>establish <strong>rigorous bounds</strong> on the number of operations required to solve a linear program</li>
      <li>simplex method</li>
      <li>interior-point method</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

